-- Commerzbank New Mortgages May Grow 20 Percent a Year, FAZ Says
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-06-04T19:39:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-04/commerzbank-new-mortgages-may-grow-20-percent-a-year-faz-says.html
Commerzbank AG (CBK)  sees “good chances”
for increasing the amount of mortgages by 20 percent annually in
coming years as well as its market share,  Frankfurter Allgemeine
Zeitung  reported, citing an interview with Michael Mandel, head
of private customers at Commerzbank.  The lender expanded its mortgage business by 20 percent to
4.7 billion euros ($5.9 billion) last year, the newspaper said
in a preview of an article to be published tomorrow. In March
this year alone, new business totaled about 500 million euros,
the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
